# Copy this file to `.env` and uncomment what you need: `./.env` is
# loaded at boot by the application and the migration CLI, and is never
# committed (see .gitignore). Comments use `#` — the only comment
# character the dotenv syntax knows; a present but malformed `.env`
# aborts the boot instead of being silently half-read.
#
# Every key has a sane default in common/src/config.rs; the variables
# below are overrides (prefix APP_, separator __), shared by the api and
# the migration CLI. Unknown APP_* keys abort the boot on purpose: a
# typoed override must never be silently ignored.

# Application identity, defaulting to the binary's Cargo.toml name and
# version. Override only for display purposes (e.g. a per-environment
# name); the version normally follows the build.
# APP_NAME=starterhub-rust-stack
# APP_VERSION=0.0.0

# Deployment environment, strictly one of: local, development, staging,
# production (no short forms, no case variants). The interactive
# documentation (/docs) is only exposed in local and development. The
# Docker image overrides this to production — and production refuses to
# boot with the default database password.
# APP_ENVIRONMENT=local

# Verbose telemetry: DEBUG level instead of INFO.
# APP_DEBUG=true

# HTTP server. The timeout is the per-request upper bound in seconds.
# APP_SERVER__HOST=0.0.0.0
# APP_SERVER__PORT=8080
# APP_SERVER__TIMEOUT=30

# PostgreSQL target.
# APP_DATABASE__HOST=localhost
# APP_DATABASE__PORT=5432
# APP_DATABASE__USERNAME=root
# APP_DATABASE__PASSWORD=root
# APP_DATABASE__DATABASE=app

# PostgreSQL pool tuning (durations in seconds).
# APP_DATABASE__POOL__MAX_CONNECTIONS=100
# APP_DATABASE__POOL__MIN_CONNECTIONS=5
# APP_DATABASE__POOL__CONNECT_TIMEOUT=8
# APP_DATABASE__POOL__ACQUIRE_TIMEOUT=8
# APP_DATABASE__POOL__IDLE_TIMEOUT=600
# APP_DATABASE__POOL__MAX_LIFETIME=1800
